SHG Multilingual Chatbot

An AI-powered multilingual chatbot built for rural women's **Self-Help Groups (SHGs)** in India. It helps users access information about government schemes, loans, savings, and financial literacy — in **any language**, with **voice input and output**.

Features

Multilingual — Ask in Tamil, Hindi, Telugu, English, or any language
Voice Input — Speak your question using your microphone
Voice Output — Hear the answer read aloud in your language
Gemini AI — Powered by Google's Gemini 1.5 Pro
Chat History — View the full conversation in the session
Simple UI — Built with Streamlit for easy access

Tech Stack

*Component        
    Frontend / UI  
    AI Model        
    Voice Input    
    Voice Output    
    Translation     
    Language Detect 

*Technology
    Streamlit 
    Google Gemini 1.5 Pro
    SpeechRecognition + PyAudio 
    gTTS (Google Text-to-Speech)
    deep-translator (Google Translate)
    langdetect 

Setup & Installation

1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Aslin-Jerika/shg-multilingual-chatbot.git
cd shg-multilingual-chatbot

2. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Set your Gemini API Key
Create a `.env` file in the project root:
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_api_key_here
Get your free API key at: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey

4. Run the app
streamlit run shg_chatbot.py


